<TITLE> Khaleda addresses Rajshahi rally Wednesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, May 4 (bdnews24.com)  BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia will be addressing a rally in Rajshahi on Wednesday afternoon. Goyeshwar Chandra Roy, party standing committee member and chief coordinator of the divisional-level rally, told a press conference at a Rajshahi restaurant that Khaleda would deliver a speech dealing with law and order, gas, power and water crisis, price situation, treaties with India and the Bhola by-election. He said leaders and activists of all districts in Rajshahi division would attend the rally, to be held at city's madrasa ground at 2pm. The Rajshahi meeting is part of BNP's planned divisional-level rallies, following rallies in Chittagong and Khulna. Goyeshwar said the party chief would start for Rajshahi from Dhaka at 9am to attend the rally, which is being presided over by BNP joint secretary general and former Rajshahi mayor Mizanur Rahman Minu. Security has been beefed up in Rajshahi before Khaleda's visit. City Special Branch assistant commissioner Tariqul Islam told bdnews24.com that 'three-tier' security would be arranged in and around the rally. A large number of law enforcers, including 900 police, RAB and security agency personnel, would be deployed, he said. Tariqul said eight close-circuit cameras have been installed to keep watch on the rally ground. bd
